Full Description: Founded in 2002, ADI Energy’s sole business is the provision of energy services to its customers. ADI Energy primarily began as an energy services consulting firm, growing steadily and profitably during its first few years while always adding and retaining qualified professional staff. The vision of the founding employee, John Rizzo, PE, was to create a company that could deliver higher-value projects to clients by combining the same suite of services offered by the largest ESCO’s, but with the veracity, flexibility, clarity, cost-consciousness and customer focus of a small company. Beginning in 2008, ADI Energy started to integrate design/build services into its offerings and by 2011 had evolved into a comprehensive energy services company (ESCO) and became a DOE Qualified ESCO. Today, ADI Energy is a specialized design-build energy-engineering firm with in-house project execution capabilities. ADI’s team of experienced energy professionals are ready to develop, build and deliver complex capital projects whose savings directly fall to the bottom line. ADI’s core business: technically strong energy solutions, with design and engineering under one roof. ADI Energy has a special emphasis on designing resources to support its clients with energy efficiency, renewable energy, and commissioning of existing systems. Our staff includes registered professional engineers (PE) who have been involved in the ESCO business for over 25 years, with specific experience in renewable energy, engineering development, CX and design/build services.

Full Description: Letifly's Story Bonded by their love of beautiful objects and home decor, Leti and Raphael embarked on their design journey in 2018. After seeing the results for their own apartment decor (and their wallet!), they decided to create a website to share their finds to design lovers. We are always looking for fresh ideas and welcome creators to contact us for more information on how to be a part of Letifly.

No government, religion, brand, or company has been left untouched by this movement. Over 100 retail industry senior executives surveyed by KPMG in 2013 reported that social media is the #1 most impactful technology trend on their business.  We believe the term “consumer” will soon be retired to the history books as fewer and fewer people consume what they’re sold or do what they’re told.  Socially-enlightened brands work with 8thBridge because they not only recognize this new world order, but are ready to embrace it and begin reshaping their business around people.  8thBridge provides a proven path to social monetization for marketing and ecommerce executives that have not been satisfied with their ability to translate fans and followers into measurable sales lift.  8thBridge was recognized by the Always On Global 250 in 2011 as one of the top 250 private companies in the world.  8thBridge is headquartered in Minneapolis, MN. Since its founding in 2008, world class brands like Ticketmaster, 7 For All Mankind, Delta Air Lines, Oscar de la Renta, Electronic Arts, and many others have partnered with 8thBridge.  8thBridge is funded by Split Rock Partners and Trident Capital.

Our BtoB wholesale platform working from a simple premise. On one side, the number of local and healthier food brands is exploding, yet they struggle to get discovered by consumers through wholesale channels. On the other side, neighborhood stores are looking for new sources of revenues and have in general a huge amount of underused shelf space. This opportunity to connect the right brands, with the right retail at the right time is the win-win model we are building.
